doc.after: The economy of the Iroquois also known as Haudenosaunee historically was based on communal production and combined elements of both horticulture and hunter gatherer systems The tribes of the Iroquois Confederacy and other Northern Iroquoian speaking peoples including the Huron had their traditional territory in what is now New York State and the southern areas bordering the Great Lakes
